-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest
-- 
-- Mon Mar 24, 2014 12:05AM EDT
-- None



March 24 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* Two of Morocco's biggest banks, BMCE <BMCE.CS> and BCP <BCP.CS> are preparing to launch Islamic subsidiaries as the Moroccan parliament discusses a bill regulating Islamic banks and sukuk issues, banking sources said. [ID:nL5N0MK0KE]  * British utility Thames Water has begun a hunt for international investors to pay for the construction of a 15-mile (24-kilometre) "super-sewer" in London, a British newspaper reported, without citing sources. [ID:nL4N0ML0EP]  * Apple Inc <AAPL.O> is in talks with Comcast Corp <CMCSA.O> to enter into a deal for a streaming-television service that would allow Apple set-top boxes to bypass congestion on the web, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL4N0ML0G2]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]